. Reviews and insightsOverall, TaxJar has some mixed reviews. Their Shopify app has roughly 100 reviews and only has a three-star rating (out of five stars), with many users complaining about customer service. However, TaxJar has 4.4 stars (out of five) based on more than 75 reviews on Capterra, with users saying that the program was easy to implement. This indicates that using their Shopify app might be a little tricky, but there’s a good chance you’ll have a good overall experience with the company. What is Anrok?Anrok is a very popular sales tax solution designed with SaaS companies in mind. It is especially popular among startups looking to outsource compliance.Unlike many competitors, like Avalara, that are more general-purpose solutions, Anrok is built to address the unique problems faced by SaaS companies. The SaaS space is constantly changing, especially in terms of sales tax, and Anrok is focused on growing and changing with this space. Core features of AnrokAnrok’s features were designed to provide SaaS businesses with the tools and techniques that are needed to navigate the complexities of SaaS sales tax, such as:Sales tax compliance: Ensures that businesses remain compliant with varying state laws that govern taxation of software and subscription services.Sales tax calculation: Provides accurate, real-time calculations that account for the unique rules applied to SaaS products, including tiered taxation and exemptions.Nexus tracking: Monitors where a business has established nexus, based on customer locations and revenue thresholds, which are especially critical for subscription-based models.Filing and remittance: Automates the preparation, filing, and remittance of sales tax returns, reducing administrative burdens and ensuring timely submissions.Exemption certificate management: Tracks and validates exemption certificates for B2B customers, ensuring compliance while streamlining the sales process.Much like TaxJar, Anrok has the ability to integrate with the other software that your business relies on. Anrok comes with no-code integrations for billing platforms such as Quickbooks, Stripe, Xero, Chargebee, Recurly, and Chargify. It also has no-code integrations for payroll and HR systems such as Rippling, Gusto, and BambooHR (important when it comes to tracking physical nexus). And like many players in the space, Anrok provides API support, so no matter what systems your company uses, you can integrate Anrok into your stack. This makes Anrok incredibly flexible and implementable at pretty much any SaaS company. Pricing and getting startedAnrok offers only custom pricing tailored to a business’s size, transaction volume, and specific requirements. So you’ll need to book a demo with an Anrok representative to learn about pricing. However, there are three main plans; Starter, Core, and Growth. It’s important to mention that you will not receive API technical consultations if you go with the Starter plan!While Anrok no longer publicly discloses pricing, using Wayback Machine, we are able historical pricing for the above-mentioned tiers:Who is Anrok best for?Since Anrok is designed specifically with SaaS businesses in mind, it’s the ideal choice for companies that sell subscription-based products. It’s particularly valuable for businesses that operate in multiple states or internationally, as this is often when sales taxes become the most confusing, regardless of the type of business you’re running. Reviews and insightsOverall, Anrok has very good reviews online; its score on G2 is 4.5 stars (out of five), based on more than 150 reviews. Existing customers seem to be huge fans of how easy the product is to use, the level of customer service they receive, and the integrations that are offered.Read more: 6 popular Anrok alternatives comparedNumeral: A third option to considerAlthough TaxJar and Anrok are great options for sales tax compliance, Numeral is a more versatile alternative that bridges the gap between these two tools. Numeral is designed to serve businesses of all shapes and sizes that sell both products and services. This makes it a great choice for companies that have hybrid business models (or may in the future).How does Numeral compare with TaxJar and Anrok?Numeral provides similar services and has many of the same features as TaxJar and Anrok, including:Sales tax compliance and calculation: Handles real-time tax rate calculations and ensures compliance across jurisdictions.Nexus tracking and filing: Tracks nexus and automates the preparation and submission of tax returns, providing end-to-end compliance.Cross-platform compatibility: Integrates with a wide range of platforms, including e-commerce systems like Shopify and subscription billing platforms like Stripe, making it versatile and useful for e-commerce businesses and SaaS businesses.Additionally, the user-friendly interface, adaptable features, and top-notch customer service make Numeral incredibly easy to integrate into your stack. This makes it a great choice for small and midsize businesses that are looking for both ease of use and flexibility. Pricing and getting startedNumeral’s pricing is straightforward and doesn’t have any hidden fees, so you don’t have to worry about calculating your monthly cost based on how many orders you receive. Instead, Numeral charges a flat fee of $150 to register your business in a particular state. For context, TaxJar charges $299 per registration. Once your business is registered, Numeral charges a flat fee of $75 per filing, regardless of your company’s revenue or how many orders it receives.[blog-post-inline-cta]Which sales tax compliance tool is right for me?Unfortunately, there isn’t really a clear choice when it comes to choosing the right sales tax compliance tool. The product that works best for you is going to depend on a lot of things, like your own personal preferences, your company’s structure, and how much business your company does. Generally speaking, TaxJar is a great choice for e-commerce companies, and Anrok is great for SaaS companies. However, if you’re looking for a solution that works with both types of business models, then Numeral is probably right for you. Numeral is a flexible alternative, allowing you to operate a hybrid business model with ease, or simply leave the door open for future expansion. If you are looking for additional options, you may want to compare Avalara and Anrok, too.About the author
























